# FFresco Frontend Rules

Follow the canonical docs:

```txt
docs/01-frontend-architecture-standard.md
docs/02-ui-component-standard.md
docs/03-api-integration-standard.md
docs/04-modal-toast-standard.md
docs/05-testing-strategy.md
```

Core rules:

```txt
1. Do not call fetch directly from visual components.
2. Use services/api layer for backend calls.
3. Use /v1 backend routes only.
4. Pages orchestrate; components render.
5. Reuse common UI components before creating new ones.
6. Do not create ad hoc modal/toast patterns.
7. Keep mocks aligned with backend contracts.
8. Implement one PR scope at a time.
9. Avoid broad refactors unless explicitly requested.
10. Preserve existing UI behavior unless the ticket says otherwise.
```
